<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1322,1794,1900]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Coloration dark green in life, preserved specimens blackish green to reddish brown. Dark green specimens with paler spots at apex of each claval vein. Forewing with brownish suffusion on clavus continued to apex.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1322,284,350]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Veins margined by circular pits, those bordering claval veins more dense. Male eighth sternite large, hind margin medially slightly convex, devoid of setae.</paragraph>
