<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1323,284,1230]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis box="[312,414,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks</emphasis>
: The two females from Sikkim are very dark green in life and were collected on a shrub bordering a narrow stream of water on a steep slope. The females from Ruby mines including the 
<typeStatus box="[515,566,1084,1110]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
are reddish brown; the male is more ochraceous brown. Two males of an undescribed species of 
<taxonomicName box="[688,779,1124,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gessius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[688,779,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Gessius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[854,956,1124,1150]" name="Taiwan" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Formosa</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[973,1063,1124,1150]" name="Taiwan" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
) were also examined. Darker spots described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant" box="[593,768,1164,1190]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" refString="Distant W. L. (1908) Rhynchota-Homoptera In: Bingham, C. T. (ed.) The fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Volume IV, 501 p. Taylor &amp; Francis, London." type="book" year="1908">
Distant (
<number box="[698,759,1164,1190]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1908.0">1908</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
on the scutellum were not found in the 
<typeStatus box="[1271,1321,1164,1190]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
specimen examined.
</paragraph>
